.SH DESCRIPTION
.B knetutils
is a single-binary suite of advanced network utilities designed with zero magic numbers, safe memory management, and cross-platform BPF/AF_PACKET abstractions.
.PP
The suite includes the following commands:
.TP
.B arping
Send ARP requests to a neighbor host.
.TP
.B ping
Send ICMP ECHO_REQUEST to network hosts.
.TP
.B sniff
A minimal packet sniffer for capturing and inspecting L2/L3/L4 traffic.
.TP
.B tcping
Measure TCP connection latency to a specific port.
.TP
.B traceroute
Trace the route to a remote host using UDP or ICMP probes.
.SH OPTIONS
To view specific options for a command, run:
.PP
.RS
.B knetutils
.I command
.B \-h
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
knetutils developers.
